On June 9, 2010, the President signed several bills into law. These include H.R. 2711, which allows for payment of transportation and moving expenses for the immediate family of certain Federal employees who die in the line of duty. Other bills signed into law include H.R. 3250, designating a United States Postal Service facility in Riverhead, New York, as the "Private First Class Garfield M. Langhorn Post Office Building," and H.R. 3634, designating a facility in Swifton, Arkansas, as the "George Kell Post Office." Additionally, various other facilities across the country were designated as post offices in honor of individuals. Lastly, H.R. 5330 extends provision for limited civil antitrust liability for participants in the Justice Department's corporate leniency program until June 22, 2020.